---
import Terminal from './Terminal.astro';
---
<section id="platform" class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="fade-up">
      <p class="section-label">Platform Components</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Six building blocks of an Agent-Native CI</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle mb-24">
        Each component works standalone. Together, they form the infrastructure your AI agents need to ship with confidence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">

      {/* 00 - Visdom Maturity Matrix */}
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="component-number">00</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">
              Visdom Maturity Matrix
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              60 practices across 4 perspectives and 5 maturity levels. Know exactly where your organization stands on AI readiness — and what to improve next.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Interactive Assessment</span>
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">Workshop Mode</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://visdom-ai-maturity-matrix.pages.dev/assessment" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">Try the Assessment</a>
              <a href="https://visdom-ai-maturity-matrix.pages.dev/matrix/development" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Explore Matrix</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card accent-card p-8 flex items-center justify-center">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap justify-center">
              {['Ad-hoc', 'Guided', 'Systematic', 'Optimized', 'Autonomous'].map((level, i) => (
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <div class="text-center px-4 py-3 rounded-xl transition-transform hover:scale-105" style={`background: ${['var(--color-maturity-0)','var(--color-maturity-1)','var(--color-maturity-2)','var(--color-maturity-3)','var(--color-maturity-4)'][i]}; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px ${['rgba(0,0,0,0.04)','rgba(13,148,136,0.08)','rgba(5,150,105,0.08)','rgba(22,163,74,0.08)','rgba(34,197,94,0.1)'][i]}`}>
                    <div class="text-sm font-bold" style={`color: ${ ['#71717a','#0d9488','var(--color-emerald-dark)','#16a34a','#22c55e'][i]}`}>L{i+1}</div>
                    <div class="text-[10px] mt-0.5" style={`color: ${ ['#71717a','#0d9488','var(--color-emerald-dark)','#16a34a','#22c55e'][i]}; opacity: 0.8`}>{level}</div>
                  </div>
                  {i < 4 && (
                    <svg width="20" height="8" class="text-border hidden sm:block"><path d="M0 4h20" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/></svg>
                  )}
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* 01 - Visdom Context Fabric */}
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <Terminal title="vidia">
{`$ vidia init
Scanning repository...
Detected: pyproject.toml, .pre-commit-config.yaml,
          GitHub Actions, Docker Compose, ArchUnit
Found 23 rules across 6 categories.
Exported to CLAUDE.md `}<span class="text-emerald">&#x2713;</span>{`

$ vidia expert src/auth/login.py
Expert: @jkowalski (score: 0.87)
Last touch: 3 days ago
Bus factor: 1 ⚠
Blast radius: 12 files`}
            </Terminal>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="component-number">01</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">
              Visdom Context Fabric
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Structured, agent-consumable context built across repositories and teams. Who knows this code? What breaks if I change it? Your agents stop hallucinating when they can actually see your codebase.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">Visdom Developer Intelligence</span> — deterministic code expertise, blast radius analysis, and ownership graphs via MCP.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Open Source</span>
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">MCP Server</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">CLI</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://github.com/VirtusLab/visdom-developer-intelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">View on GitHub</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/VirtusLab/visdom-developer-intelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Documentation</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* 02 - Visdom Code Review (VCR) */}
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="component-number">02</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">
              Visdom Code Review
              <span class="text-base font-normal text-text-muted">VCR</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Code review that understands your architecture. VCR catches boundary violations, security issues, and performance regressions before they hit production — with context-aware analysis that goes beyond linting.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Architecture</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">Security</span>
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Performance</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://virtuslab.github.io/visdom-code-review/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">Read the Reference</a>
              <a href="https://virtuslab.github.io/visdom-code-review/before-after/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Before / After</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <Terminal title="vcr">
{`$ vcr analyze --pr 142
Scanning diff... 23 files changed

◉ Architecture  3 findings
  ├─ Service boundary violation in OrderService
  ├─ Missing retry policy on external call
  └─ Circular dependency introduced

◉ Security      1 finding
  └─ Unvalidated input in /api/webhook

◉ Performance   2 findings
  ├─ N+1 query in UserRepository.findAll()
  └─ Missing index on orders.status

Summary: 6 findings across 3 categories
`}<span class="text-emerald">Review ready ✓</span>
            </Terminal>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* 03 - Visdom Governance */}
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <div class="card accent-card p-8">
              <div class="space-y-5">
                {[
                  { label: 'Trace', desc: 'Session traces, token usage, tool calls, secret redaction', color: 'var(--color-emerald)' },
                  { label: 'Enforce', desc: 'Model allowlists, path protection, token budgets', color: 'var(--color-blue)' },
                  { label: 'Audit', desc: 'Ed25519 signatures, hash-chained records, SOX/PCI-DSS', color: 'var(--color-purple)' },
                  { label: 'Evaluate', desc: 'Auto-evaluation, model distribution, adoption patterns', color: 'var(--color-amber)' },
                  { label: 'Attribute', desc: 'Line-by-line AI code attribution via tree-sitter', color: 'var(--color-emerald)' },
                ].map(item => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3 group">
                    <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full mt-1.5 shrink-0 transition-transform group-hover:scale-150" style={`background: ${item.color}`}></span>
                    <div>
                      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-text">{item.label}</span>
                      <span class="text-xs text-text-muted ml-2">{item.desc}</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="component-number">03</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">
              Visdom Governance
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              You can't govern what you can't see. A tamper-evident record of every AI agent interaction — tracing, evaluation, and attribution — wired into EU AI Act compliance reporting.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">TraceVault</span> — a flight recorder for AI development with Ed25519-signed, hash-chained records and line-by-line AI attribution.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">Tracing</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Audit Trail</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">EU AI Act</span>
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Auto-Evaluation</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3">
              <a href="https://tracevault.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-primary text-sm">tracevault.dev</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/softwaremill/tracevault" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">GitHub</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* 04 - Visdom Security */}
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="component-number">04</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4">
              Visdom Security
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              AI agents need room to experiment without breaking things — and without becoming the breach. Ephemeral, fully isolated execution environments with policy guardrails, secret redaction, and zero blast radius into production.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              Powered by <span class="font-semibold text-text">Sandcat</span> — lightweight, disposable sandboxes built for agentic workflows, with scoped credentials and egress controls.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-emerald/10 text-emerald border border-emerald/20">Isolation</span>
              <span class="tag bg-blue/10 text-blue border border-blue/20">Policy Guardrails</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Zero Blast Radius</span>
            </div>
            <a href="#contact" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Learn More &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <div>
            <Terminal title="sandcat">
{`$ sandcat create --from main --policy strict
Creating isolated environment...
  ├─ Cloning repository        ✓
  ├─ Provisioning services     ✓
  ├─ Scoped credentials        ✓
  ├─ Egress allowlist applied  ✓
  └─ Agent access configured   ✓

Sandbox ready: sb-a1b2c3
Agent can execute, test, and iterate
with zero blast radius into production.
`}<span class="text-emerald">Environment secured ✓</span>
            </Terminal>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* 05 - Visdom Machine CI */}
      <div class="platform-block fade-up">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
            <div class="card accent-card p-8">
              <div class="space-y-6">
                {[
                  { label: 'Build time reduction', value: '-88%', width: '88%' },
                  { label: 'PR merge time', value: '-43%', width: '43%' },
                  { label: 'Agent iteration speed', value: '50x/hr', width: '95%' },
                ].map(item => (
                  <div>
                    <div class="flex justify-between text-sm mb-2">
                      <span class="text-text-secondary">{item.label}</span>
                      <span class="font-semibold text-emerald">{item.value}</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="h-2.5 bg-surface-light rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                      <div class="h-full rounded-full progress-bar" style={`width: ${item.width}; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--color-emerald), var(--color-blue))`}></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="component-number">05</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mt-1 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
              Visdom Machine CI
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20 text-xs font-medium normal-case tracking-normal">Coming Soon</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Your CI takes 45 minutes. An AI agent iterates 50x per hour. We re-architect your pipeline to match agent speed — so the feedback loop never becomes the bottleneck.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Bazel</span>
              <span class="tag bg-purple/10 text-purple border border-purple/20">Gradle</span>
              <span class="tag bg-amber/10 text-amber border border-amber/20">Performance</span>
            </div>
            <a href="https://virtuslab.com/blog/ai/the-fallacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-pill btn-outline text-sm">Read: "The Ferrari Engine in a Fiat 500" &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
